HEADWORD: Electro-muscular
<hw>E*lec`tro-mus"cu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the reaction (contraction) of
the muscles under electricity, or their sensibility to it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electron</ent>⟦br⟧
